NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Translate this NL query into SQL: "For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them."
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid ORDER BY COUNT(version) DESC;

NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Use given schema: ModelServices(bmid, sid, version).
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid, version ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC;

NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Return one version per sid; ties allowed.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version FROM (SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS freq, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC ) AS rn FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid, version ) AS ranked WHERE rn = 1;

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt: Translate this NL query into SQL: "Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh."
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid FROM BaseModel NATURAL JOIN ModelServices WHERE creator_uid = user_iuwrh;

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt: Use joins and creator filter. Here are the relevant table schemas: ModelServices(bmid, sid, version), BaseModel(bmid, creator_uid, ...), AgentCreator(uid, ...), Users(uid, username, ...)
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT ms.sid FROM ModelServices ms JOIN BaseModel b ON ms.bmid = b.bmid WHERE b.creator_uid = (SELECT uid FROM Users WHERE username='user_iuwrh') GROUP BY ms.sid HAVING COUNT(*) = COUNT(DISTINCT b.bmid);

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
prompt: Translate this NL query to SQL using the following schema. "Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations." [Full Table Schema]
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT cm.mid FROM CustomizedModel cm WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM ModelConfigurations mc WHERE mc.bmid = cm.bmid AND mc.mid = cm.mid);
